# 11_universal_hide_show — s191 m4 universal hide/show verbs.
#
# Every curvz::widgets::* substrate widget gains `hide` / `show` /
# `visible` for free — the base ScriptableWidget intercepts them
# before the leaf's invoke()/query() runs. Adding a leaf type later
# (Label, Box, whatever) inherits the verbs automatically. Leaves
# can't forget to support them because they never see the call.
#
# This script proves it across three different leaf types:
#   - ToggleButton (Node tool on the main toolbar — tb_nod)
#   - ToggleButton (Scripter toggle in the headerbar — mw_scripter,
#                   diagnostic-only)
#   - Button       (one inspector button if a doc is open)
#
# After each hide, the script asserts visible == false; after each
# show, asserts visible == true. The widget actually disappears on
# screen — the verb writes through set_visible, the same path the
# rest of the app uses.

#[sub] First the Node toolbar button

assert tb_nod visible == true
tb_nod hide
assert tb_nod visible == false

#[sub] Now bring it back

tb_nod show
assert tb_nod visible == true

#[sub] Now the Scripter toggle itself

assert mw_scripter visible == true
mw_scripter hide
assert mw_scripter visible == false

#[sub] And restore it

mw_scripter show
assert mw_scripter visible == true

#[sub] Done. hide/show works the same on every substrate widget.
